# SnapBudget OCR - C4 Component Architecture

## Executive Summary
SnapBudget OCR is an Android application designed to scan, parse, and categorize physical receipts into digital transactions. This documentation outlines the component-level architecture of the system, breaking down the monolithic App Container into logical components that handle UI, OCR processing, data matching, and persistence.

## System Components

### 1. UI Layer Component
- **Description**: Handles user interactions, camera preview lifecycle, dashboard visualizations (pie charts), and displaying transaction history.
- **Key Classes**: `MainActivity`, `CameraActivity`, `DashboardViewModel`, `TransactionAdapter`.
- **Interfaces**: Observes data from the Data Access Layer, triggers actions in the OCR Engine.

### 2. OCR Engine Component
- **Description**: Core engine for image processing, text extraction, structural parsing, and fallback generative AI capabilities.
- **Key Classes**: `DocumentScanner`, `ImagePreprocessor`, `OcrProcessor`, `ReceiptParser`, `GenerativeAiFallbackService`.
- **Interfaces**: Receives camera frames, outputs structured receipt data.

### 3. Matching & Categorization Component
- **Description**: Analyzes raw extracted text to normalize data, match known merchants using fuzzy logic, assign spending categories, estimate confidence, and detect outliers.
- **Key Classes**: `CategoryClassifier`, `ContextualAnalyzer`, `MerchantMatcher`, `SimilarityScorer`, `ConfidenceEstimator`.
- **Interfaces**: Accepts parsed string data, outputs enriched `Transaction` models.

### 4. Data Access Component
- **Description**: Manages persistence of transaction data using Room database architecture and provides streams (Flow/LiveData) of data to the UI.
- **Key Classes**: `AppDatabase`, `TransactionDao`, `TransactionRepository`.
- **Interfaces**: Provides CRUD operations for the `Transaction` UI.

---

## Component Relationship Diagram

```mermaid
C4Component
    title Component Diagram for SnapBudget OCR App Container

    Container_Boundary(app, "SnapBudget Android App") {
        Component(ui, "UI Layer", "Android UI/ViewModels", "Displays dashboard, handles camera preview, and renders transaction history.")
        Component(ocr, "OCR Engine", "Kotlin Modules", "Scans document, pre-processes images, extracts text blocks, and parses receipts.")
        Component(matching, "Matching & Categorization Engine", "Standard Kotlin", "Calculates confidence, parses categories, fuzzy-matches merchants, and normalizes text.")
        ComponentDb(db, "Data Access Layer", "Room SQLite", "Persists localized transaction records and categories.")
    }

    System_Ext(cameraApi, "Android CameraX API", "Hardware Camera")
    System_Ext(mlkit, "Google ML Kit", "On-device Vision/OCR API")
    System_Ext(gemini, "Generative AI Service", "Cloud Fallback API")

    Rel(ui, cameraApi, "Uses configured camera frame", "CameraX")
    Rel(ui, ocr, "Initiates scanning & processing")
    Rel(ui, db, "Observes transaction data streams")
    
    Rel(ocr, mlkit, "Processes image to text blocks")
    Rel(ocr, gemini, "Uses for low-confidence fallback extraction")
    Rel(ocr, matching, "Passes raw parsed fields for enrichment")
    
    Rel(matching, db, "Saves parsed and categorized transactions")
```

---

## Core Component Details

### OCR Engine Component
- **DocumentScanner / ImagePreprocessor**: Leverages OpenCV or native image manipulation (like Canny edge detection, perspective transform) to crop the receipt from the background.
- **ReceiptParser**: Implements rule-based extraction tailored for receipts (e.g., detecting dates, finding the largest currency amount as the total, isolating invoice numbers).

### Matching & Categorization Component
- **MerchantMatcher & SimilarityScorer**: Uses string metric algorithms (Levenshtein distance, etc.) to link fragmented OCR text to existing or known merchants.
- **CategoryClassifier**: Uses keyword mappings to categorize the assigned merchant (e.g., categorizing "Organic Basket" as "Grocery" or "Food").
- **ConfidenceEstimator**: Calculates an aggregate score defining how likely the parsed data is completely accurate. Triggers manual review flows if the score falls below a threshold.

### Data Access Component
- **TransactionRepository**: Single source of truth. Handles database insertion (via `TransactionDao`) and retrieves list records.
- **Converters**: Type converters defined for Room to serialize/deserialize custom objects stored within the Transaction entities.
